            <h2 id="about_about">About</h2>
            <p>Web4thejob Studio has been initially incepted as an add-on for
                <a href="http://web4thejob.org">Web4thejob Framework CE</a>. It's mission was to
                provide web4thejob developers with an easy and visually-driven way to design custom panels on top of the
                <a href="http://wiki.web4thejob.org/miscel/why_web4thejob#the_agile_development_lifecycle">automated UI
                    /UX engine of the framework</a>.
            </p>
            <p>Going forward though, Web4thejob Studio has gradually evolved to a stand-alone product useful not only
                to web4thejob
                developers but to any member of the ZK community. Therefore, we decided to open up the product as a
                free
                service to all ZK developers and enthusiasts.
            </p>
            <h2>Installation</h2>
            <p>Installing Web4thejob Studio is as easy as adding a few configuration lines in your
                <code>web.xml</code>
                and
                <code>zk.xml</code>
                as below:
            </p>
