            <h2>Usage</h2>
            <p>Using Web4thejob Studio is pretty straightforward: you create and modify zul pages
                seamlessly by using three supplementary ways:
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>By dragging &amp; dropping widgets on the canvas</li>
                <li>By dragging &amp; dropping widgets on the outline tree</li>
                <li>By editing the zul code directly</li>
            </ol>

            <p>Every time you hit the
                <span class="label label-primary">Parse zul</span>
                button Web4thejob Studio is saving automatically to the webapp
                directory all the pending changes of the zul page under design.
                Thus, if you are running directly from the sources (i.e. unassembled webapp), you can push your changes
                to your preferred SCM without loosing any more time! Check out
                <code>jetty:run</code>
                maven goal for more info on this.
            </p>

            <h2 id="about_features">Features</h2>
            <div class="icon-list">
